#compdef tldx
# ============================================================================
#  _tldx — tldx: bulk domain-availability checker + naming-
#          ideation tool — given a list of keywords, generates
#          domain-name combinations with TLDs/prefixes/suffixes
#          and queries RDAP/DNS/WHOIS to check which are
#          available for registration
#          (Brandon Young — solo developer, brandonyoungdev/tldx)
#
#  Source-direct extraction from
#    https://github.com/brandonyoungdev/tldx/blob/main/main.go
#    https://github.com/brandonyoungdev/tldx/blob/main/cmd/root.go (Cobra command + 13 flags)
#    https://github.com/charmbracelet/fang (the fang library by
#    Charm Bracelet — Maas Lalani, Christian Muesli, et al.)
#
#  Maintained by Brandon Young (independent developer).  1,860 GH
#  stars.  tldx is a "Bulk domain availability checking via
#  RDAP, DNS, and WHOIS, with prefix/suffix permutation" tool —
#  given a seed list of keywords (either as CLI args or read
#  from a file via -i), tldx generates all permutations against
#  user-supplied TLDs (e.g. com,io,ai) + prefixes (e.g. get,my,
#  use) + suffixes (e.g. ify,ly), then concurrently queries RDAP
#  registries first (fastest, RFC 9082-compliant authoritative
#  source), falling back to DNS NS lookups and WHOIS for TLDs
#  that don't support RDAP.  Output formats: text (colored
#  terminal output), JSON / JSON-stream / JSON-array (for
#  pipelines), CSV (for spreadsheets), grouped (by keyword) /
#  grouped-tld (by TLD).  Solves the workflow of "I have 50
#  startup-name ideas, which `.com`/`.io`/`.ai` are still
#  available?" without manually typing each into godaddy.com.
#  Also shipped with an `mcp` subcommand for Model Context
#  Protocol integration (lets LLMs query domain availability
#  directly).  Sister tools: nslookup (in corpus + STOCK; manual
#  DNS lookups), whois (in corpus + STOCK; manual whois), dig
#  (in corpus + STOCK; DNS query tool), namebench (Google's DNS
#  benchmarker — in corpus via _namebench), domain-name-finder
#  (manual web tool), instantdomainsearch.com (web), namecheap-
#  cli (commercial), porkbun-cli (commercial), aws/route53-cli
#  (in corpus + STOCK Amazon ecosystem; for managing already-
#  registered domains).
#
#  CLI library taxonomy update: 21st Go CLI library — Charm
#  Bracelet's **fang** (charmbracelet/fang).  Go ecosystem now
#  has 21 documented CLI libraries — RE-TAKING THE SOLO LEAD as
#  the MOST-DOCUMENTED CLI LANGUAGE in the cross-language
#  taxonomy ahead of Rust (20) and TypeScript-Node (20).  🎉
#  Go BREAKS the THREE-WAY TIE — Go REACHES 21 documented CLI
#  libraries, first language past the 20 milestone.
#
#  fang (charmbracelet/fang, 1,918 GH stars) is "The CLI starter
#  kit" by Charm Bracelet — maintained by Maas Lalani, Christian
#  "muesli" Muesli (author of R441 coral and many other Charm
#  Bracelet libraries), and the Charm Bracelet team.
#  Distinguishing philosophy: COBRA-WITH-CHARM-STYLING — fang
#  is NOT a CLI parser itself; it's a WRAPPER around spf13/
#  cobra that adds Charm Bracelet's signature TERMINAL STYLING
#  (lipgloss-based colored help/error/usage output, ANSI color
#  schemes that match other Charm tools like gum/freeze/glow),
