#  demand.  Use case: existing cobra-based CLIs that want
#  Charm Bracelet's polish without rewriting their command
#  tree.  Migration from cobra to fang is JUST a swap of the
#  `rootCmd.Execute()` call for `fang.Execute(ctx, rootCmd,
#  opts...)`.  Used by goreleaser/goreleaser (release-engineering
#  tool 15,830 stars — IN CORPUS via _goreleaser), brandonyoungdev/
#  tldx (1,860), litebase/litebase (distributed SQLite-backed DB
#  450 stars), jaxxstorm/tscli (Tailscale API CLI 72 stars),
#  nuonco/nuon (software vendor deployment platform 93 stars),
#  taigrr/spank, apgmckay/bumpy, Hadiasemi/bbrf (Bug bounty
#  reconnaissance — for AUTHORIZED bug-bounty engagements),
#  Fuabioo/xlq, stormlightlabs/noteleaf, ByteTheCookies/
#  CookieFarm (Attack/Defense CTF framework — for AUTHORIZED
#  CTF competitions), and many other modern Go CLIs that prefer
#  Charm Bracelet's terminal aesthetic.  fang is INSPIRED BY
#  Charm Bracelet's own internal CLI tooling (their gum/glow/
#  freeze/vhs commands all use fang as their entry layer).
