#    - `fang.WithNotifySignal(os.Interrupt, ...)` — wires up a
#      context that's cancelled when the user hits Ctrl-C; the
#      cancelled context is passed to RunE handlers via
#      `cmd.Context()` so they can clean up gracefully
#    - `fang.WithCommit(string)` — adds git commit info to
#      `--version` output (also reads VCS info from
#      runtime/debug.ReadBuildInfo if Go modules tracked it)
#    - `fang.WithoutManpage()` / `fang.WithoutCompletions()` —
#      disable fang's automatic `manpage` / `completion`
#      subcommand generation (enabled by default)
#    - `fang.WithErrorHandler(fn)` — replace fang's default
#      lipgloss error renderer with a custom function for
#      project-specific error formatting
#    - `fang.WithColorSchemeFunc(fn)` — customize the lipgloss
#      color scheme (defaults to fang.AnsiColorScheme which
#      matches other Charm Bracelet tools)
#    - `fang.WithoutCheckForUpdates()` — fang DEFAULT BEHAVIOR
#      includes a periodic check-for-updates step that pings
#      GitHub for newer versions; this option opts out (useful
