#  Usage:
#    tldx [keywords...] [options]
#    tldx <subcommand> [options]
#
#  Subcommands:
#    show-presets                   List built-in TLD presets
#                                   (popular, tech, country
#                                   codes, etc.) that can be
#                                   used with --tld-preset
#    mcp                            Run as Model Context
#                                   Protocol (MCP) server for
#                                   LLM integration (lets LLM
#                                   tools query domain
#                                   availability via MCP
#                                   stdio/socket transport)
#
#  Generation options:
#    -t, --tlds <LIST>              TLDs to check (comma-
#                                   separated, e.g. com,io,ai)
#    -p, --prefixes <LIST>          Prefixes to add (comma-
#                                   separated, e.g. get,my,use)
#    -s, --suffixes <LIST>          Suffixes to add (e.g. ify,ly)
#        --tld-preset <NAME>        Use a TLD preset (popular /
#                                   tech / countries — see
#                                   `tldx show-presets`)
#    -r, --regex                    Enable regex pattern
#                                   matching for domain keywords
#    -m, --max-domain-length <N>    Maximum length of domain
#                                   name (default: 64)
#
#  Input:
#    -i, --input <FILE>             File to read keywords from
#                                   ("-" reads from stdin; one
#                                   keyword per line)
#
#  Output filtering:
#    -a, --only-available           Show only available domains
#                                   (suppress taken ones)
#    -l, --limit <N>                Stop after finding N
#                                   available domains (default:
#                                   0 = no limit; useful for
#                                   long generation runs)
#
#  Output format:
#    -f, --format <FMT>             Output format (default:
#                                   text).  Choices: text /
#                                   json / json-stream / json-
#                                   array / csv / grouped /
#                                   grouped-tld
#        --no-color                 Disable colored terminal
#                                   output (auto when stdout
#                                   is not a TTY; respects
#                                   NO_COLOR env)
#        --show-stats               Show statistics at end of
#                                   execution (queries-per-
#                                   second, total-checked,
#                                   available-count, etc.)
#
#  Debug:
#    -v, --verbose                  Show verbose output
#                                   (per-domain query results,
#                                   timing info, RDAP/DNS/
#                                   WHOIS fallback details)
#        --dry-run                  Print domains that WOULD
#                                   BE checked without making
#                                   any network calls (useful
#                                   for previewing generation
#                                   output before running long
#                                   queries)
#
#  Meta (auto from fang):
#    -h, --help                     Show help
#        --version                  Show version (set via
